
  <sn><md>### Course Overview

This course introduces chemical reactions and processes occurring in soils and the environment, with special emphasis on soil–plant relationships, nutrient cycling, ion behavior, pollutant movement, and environmental remediation.

---
 Course Learning Outcomes (CLOs)

**CLO 1**
Demonstrate knowledge of the chemistry of different soil phases and atmospheric spheres.

**CLO 2**
Understand the significance of biochemical processes active on the Earth's surface.

**CLO 3**
Acquire knowledge about soil and environmental pollutants.

**CLO 4**
Identify and manage problem soils.
</md></sn>
